surveys_complete <- read_csv("data/surveys_complete.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   record_id = col_double(),
##   month = col_double(),
##   day = col_double(),
##   year = col_double(),
##   plot_id = col_double(),
##   species_id = col_character(),
##   sex = col_character(),
##   hindfoot_length = col_double(),
##   weight = col_double(),
##   genus = col_character(),
##   species = col_character(),
##   taxa = col_character(),
##   plot_type = col_character()
## )
surveys_plot <- ggplot(data = surveys_complete, aes(x = weight, y = hindfoot_length))

surveys_plot + geom_point()

surveys_plot + geom_point(alpha = 0.1, aes(color = species_id))

Challenge

This doesnt seem like a very good way to visualize this type of data, though it does still manage to communicate it somewhat usefully.

ggplot(data = surveys_complete, aes(x = species_id, y = weight)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = plot_type))

ggplot(data = surveys_complete, aes(x = species_id, y = weight)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.1, color = "purple") + 
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.0)

Putting the boxplot in front of the points can be accomplished by switching their relative positions around the + that links the two.

Challenges

ggplot(data = surveys_complete, aes(x = species_id, y = weight)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.1, color = "purple") + 
  geom_violin(alpha = 0.0) +
  scale_y_log10()

ggplot(data = surveys_complete, aes(x = species_id, y = hindfoot_length)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.1, color = "purple") + 
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.0)

yearly_counts <- surveys_complete %>%
  count(year, genus)

yearly_counts_graph <- 
  yearly_counts %>% 
    ggplot(mapping = aes(x = year, y = n, color = genus)) +
    geom_line()

yearly_counts_graph

yearly_counts_graph %>% 
  + facet_wrap(facets = vars(genus))

yearly_sex_counts <- surveys_complete %>%
                     count(year, genus, sex)

ggplot(data = yearly_sex_counts, mapping = aes(x = year, y = n, color = sex)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(facets =  vars(genus))

ggplot(data = yearly_sex_counts, 
       mapping = aes(x = year, y = n, color = sex)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(rows = vars(sex), cols =  vars(genus))

ggplot(data = yearly_sex_counts, 
       mapping = aes(x = year, y = n, color = sex)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(rows = vars(genus))

 ggplot(data = yearly_sex_counts, 
        mapping = aes(x = year, y = n, color = sex)) +
     geom_line() +
     facet_wrap(vars(genus)) +
     theme_bw()

Challenge

avg_yearly_weight <- surveys_complete %>% 
   group_by(year, species_id) %>%
   summarize(avg_weight = mean(weight))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'year' (override with `.groups` argument)
ggplot(data = avg_yearly_weight, aes(x = year, y = avg_weight)) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(vars(species_id))

ggplot(data = yearly_sex_counts, aes(x = year, y = n, color = sex)) +
    geom_line() +
    facet_wrap(vars(genus)) +
    labs(title = "Observed Genera Through Time",
         x = "Year of Observation",
         y = "Number of Individuals") + 
    theme_bw() + 
    theme(text = element_text(size = 16))

Challenge
